JOS – Plateau state government has threatened to deal ruthlessly with Kidnappers, land grabbers and other criminal elements that wants to test will of government of Governor Simon Lalong on the Plateau The Special Adviser on Public Affairs to governor Lalong, Hon Diket Plang gave this warning in an interview with newsmen in Jos. Plang, a former Plateau lawmaker stated that in it’s quest to address the security challenges facing the state, the government has put in place various mechanism to tame activities of retrogresive elements out of the Plateau state. 2023: PDP Set To Take Over Lagos As Ayu, Saraki, Wike, Makinde,… I’m Not Seeking To Be President, I Want To Be APC Chairman… He hinted that the peace building agency established by Governor Lalong administration has done a lot in terms of peace building on Plateau. According to him,” The anti-,kidnapping and land grabbing law was also part of the effort to fight these menaces ” He added that the security Agencies in the state have continued to give suspected criminals hot Chase on the Plateau on the directive of the Governor thereby making some arrests with prosecutions on-going. “Governor Lalong in the last 6 and half years has maintained security as his cardinal priority. He rejigged and revamped the Operation Rainbow; introduced Community Policing; Created Plateau Peace Building Agency; created more synergy between the State and Security Agencies in the State; Established the State Inter religious Council; Purchased and distributed hundreds of security vehicles, Motorcycles and other equipment to all security organs in the State ” He also signed into law the Anti Kidnapping bill; Built Watchtowers in strategic places in the city; empowered and engaged more vigilantes; signed into law the anti land grabbing bill and the anti violence bill; lobbied for the establishment of Mobile Barracks in Shandam and Airforce Base in Kerang” Plang stressed. POLL Plang dismissed the insinuation that is going round in some quarters on the Plateau that the state government was not doing enough to address challenges of insecurity in the state adding that the relative peace being enjoyed by the citizens of the state is due to the doggedness and determination of the state government to ensure lasting peace on the Plateau.